# LLM Evaluation (DeepEval)

Standalone benchmark for LLM response quality. **Not** part of pytest or coverage.

## Layout

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `backend/eval/dataset.py` | `EvalCase` definitions (question, expected_output, expected_source) |
| `backend/eval/runner.py` | HTTP client: auth, SSE chat, audit log extraction |
| `backend/eval/metrics.py` | DeepEval metrics per case (judge: gpt-4o) |
| `backend/eval/run_deepeval.py` | CLI logic and JSON report |
| `backend/eval/cleanup.py` | Delete eval users from Postgres (cascade) |
| `backend/app/scripts/run_deepeval.py` | Thin entry point only |
| `usecases/agent-manual-tests.md` | Human-readable spec for all 10 cases |

## Isolation rules

- Keep all eval code in `backend/eval/` — never under `app/` except the thin script wrapper.
- Do **not** add eval tests to `tests/` or register eval in `pytest.ini`.
- Do **not** add DeepEval to `requirements.txt` (Docker prod image); dev only in `requirements-dev.txt`.
- Generated artifacts (`eval_report.json`, `.deepeval/`) are gitignored.

## Running

Requires live stack + ingested PDFs + `OPENAI_API_KEY`:

```bash
docker compose up --build
docker compose exec backend python -m app.scripts.ingest_documents --force
cd backend && python -m app.scripts.run_deepeval --base-url http://localhost:8000
```

Eval users (`eval_*@test.com`) are deleted automatically after each run (cascade removes sessions, messages, audit logs). Use `--keep-eval-data` to retain them for debugging. Cleanup uses `DATABASE_URL` from `backend/.env` — it must match the same Postgres as the API (Docker Compose maps db to host port **5400**, not 5432; see `backend/.env.example`).

Remove stale eval users from past runs:

```bash
cd backend && python -c "from eval.cleanup import delete_stale_eval_users; print(delete_stale_eval_users())"
```

## Adding a new case

1. Add the scenario to `usecases/agent-manual-tests.md` (question, expected source, pass criteria).
2. Append an `EvalCase` to `EVAL_CASES` in `backend/eval/dataset.py`.
3. Register metrics in `backend/eval/metrics.py` via `_METRICS_BY_CASE`.
4. Re-run the benchmark and update the results table in `README.md`.

## Metric conventions

- **Pass gate** (case pass/fail): `FaithfulnessMetric` + case-specific `GEval` only.
- **Informational** (reported, not gating): `AnswerRelevancyMetric`, `ContextualRelevancyMetric`, `HallucinationMetric`.
- Use `LLMTestCaseParams` for `GEval` (deepeval 3.x; requires `openai>=1.68.0`).
- Judge model: `GPTModel(model="gpt-4o")` — configure once in `metrics.py`.

## Runner conventions

- One fresh chat session per case (no history bleed).
- Parse SSE from `POST /api/v1/chat/conversations/{id}/messages` (`turn_started` → `done`).
- Build `retrieval_context` from audit log `"Tool Result"` entries (`data.results[].text`).
- Set both `retrieval_context` and `context` on `LLMTestCase` (Faithfulness vs Hallucination metrics).
- Record `completion_time_ms` per case (end-to-end chat request) and include audit-log `latency_ms` breakdown for LLM/tool calls in the report.

## Do not

- Mock the LLM or RAG in eval — this is an integration benchmark against the live API.
- Couple eval logic into `ChatService`, agents, or routes.
- Fail `pytest` or lower coverage when extending the eval suite.
